"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The code uses set_xticks() and set_xticklabels() with the unique dates from the DataFrame, which may not correspond to the actual ticks set by MonthLocator(). This can lead to misalignment of tick labels with the ticks themselves. Instead, the ticks should be set according to the locator's output.\", \"patch\": \"19,20c19,20\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> ax.set_xticks(ax.get_xticks())\\n> ax.set_xticklabels(labels=[date.strftime('%Y-%m') for date in ax.get_xticks()], rotation=45)\\n\"}"